article.headline: Marshall scores 29 as Albany (NY) beats New Hampshire 86-79
article.description: — Amar'e Marshall scored 29 points as Albany (NY) beat New Hampshire 86-79 on Saturday.
article.linkText: Marshall scores 29 as Albany (NY) beats New Hampshire 86-79
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- — Amar'e Marshall scored 29 points as Albany (NY) beat New Hampshire 86-79 on Saturday. Marshall added six rebounds for the Great Danes (11-10, 3-3 America East Conference). Sebastian Thomas scored 25 points while shooting 5 for 15 (1 for 5 from 3-point range) and 14 of 15 from the free throw line, and added seven assists and six steals. Jonathan Beagle had 14 points and finished 6 of 7 from the field. Clarence O. Daniels II led the way for the Wildcats (12-8, 4-3) with 21 points, eight rebounds and two steals. New Hampshire also got 19 points, four assists and two steals from Ahmad Robinson. In addition, Jaxson Baker finished with 16 points and two blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
